checker.sourceparser
Class ParserComments

java.lang.Object
  checker.sourceparser.ParserComments

public class ParserComments
extends java.lang.Object

ParserComments scans source code comments and writes them to array. This class also provide variable searching from the line. This class is used for all source parsers

findVariableSection

protected SourceParserLine findVariableSection(SourceParserLine pLine)
This method is searching quotation and apostrophe marks that usually indicates variable in the declaration. If either mark is found, method set section started. When quotation or apostrophe section is set true, comments or references are not parsed.

Parameters:
SourceParserLine - pLine is code line object that includes line and positions

endVariableSection

protected SourceParserLine endVariableSection(SourceParserLine pLine)
This method is searching quotation and apostrophe second mark to reset apostrophe or quotation section. If either mark is found, method reset section (false).

Parameters:
SourceParserLine - pLine is code line object that includes line and positions
